http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Unclaimed-bag-at-airport-leads-to-tense-moments/article14026825.ece

Close on the heels of a threat letter found in an Air Asia domestic flight, an unclaimed bag found near the entrance of Kempegowda International Airport created panic among visitors on Friday.The unclaimed bag was found by the airport police during routine checks, based on which an alert was announced and the area cordoned off.The anti-sabotage squad was pressed into service and it examined examined the contents in the bag.P.S. Harsha, Deputy Commissioner of Police (North east) confirmed the incident adding that there was no cause for concern.